erumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08070311/DT-Swiss-ARC-rim-brake-aero-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_new-aero-180-hubs-120x72.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08070311/DT-Swiss-ARC-rim-brake-aero-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_new-aero-180-hubs-768x461.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08070311/DT-Swiss-ARC-rim-brake-aero-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_new-aero-180-hubs-696x418.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08070311/DT-Swiss-ARC-rim-brake-aero-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_new-aero-180-hubs-1068x641.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08070311/DT-Swiss-ARC-rim-brake-aero-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_new-aero-180-hubs-700x420.jpg 700w\"></a></p><p>A new Dicut Aero rim brake specific hub shell with lower drag has been refined for the new wheels, to transition smoothly with the new spokes to make the new ARC wheels faster. To-tier ARC 1100 wheels get premium SINC ceramic bearings in 180 series hubs, while the more affordable ARC 1400 gets 240 hubs with steel bearings.</p><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/2020-DT-Swiss-Ratchet-EXP-fewer-moving-parts_new-180-straight-pull-hub_cutaway.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/2020-DT-Swiss-Ratchet-EXP-fewer-moving-parts_new-180-straight-pull-hub_cutaway.jpg\" alt=\"new DT Swiss Ratchet EXP star rings how have a fixed side with only one spring-loaded ratchet\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/2020-DT-Swiss-Ratchet-EXP-fewer-moving-parts_new-180-straight-pull-hub_cutaway.jpg 1600w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/2020-DT-Swiss-Ratchet-EXP-fewer-moving-parts_new-180-str