.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08070304/DT-Swiss-ARC-rim-brake-aero-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_three-depths-1920x946.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08070304/DT-Swiss-ARC-rim-brake-aero-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_three-depths-853x420.jpg 853w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08070304/DT-Swiss-ARC-rim-brake-aero-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_three-depths-324x160.jpg 324w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-264426\">new ARC rim brake wheels: 48, 62 &amp; 80mm deep</figcaption></figure><p>One thing that hasn’t really changed are the proven blunt U-shape carbon rim profiles developed alongside aerodynamics specialists Swiss Side. Essentially DT &amp; Swiss Side decided not to mess with the already wide &amp; fast rims, since many rim brake bikes don’t have much extra room to play with, leaving it to the rest of the wheel build to make the new wheels faster.</p><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles-600x450.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/DT-Swiss_ARC-1100_RoadRevolution18_SwissSide_aerodynamic-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_rim-profiles-600x450.jpg 600w\"></a></p><p>The wheels are still 17mm internal, with full carbon hooked, tubeless-ready beads. And they are available in the same three aero-optimized depths: 48, 62 &amp; 80mm.</p><h3>DT Swiss ARC rim brake – Wheelset pricing, availability &amp; options</h3><figure id=\"attachment_264425\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-264425\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08070257/DT-Swiss-ARC-rim-brake-aero-carbon-tubeless-road-wheels_ARC-1100-Dicut-RB-wheels.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/08070257/DT-Swiss-